    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-2929811",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "2929811",
                "title": "Figure 1",
                "abstract": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A plane and its properties "
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A plane defines a flat surface in the x- and y-axis dimensions of its local coordinate space according to its "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnplane/1523782-width"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnplane/1522837-height"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " properties. To orient a plane differently, adjust the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnnode/1407964-transform"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of the node containing the plane geometry. You can create a rounded rectangular plane using the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnplane/1523005-cornerradius"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The surface is one-sided. Its surface normal vectors point in the positive z-axis direction of its local coordinate space, so it is only visible from that direction by default. To render both sides of a plane, either set the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnmaterial/1462531-doublesided"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of its material to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " or create two plane geometries and orient them back to back."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Control the level of detail with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnplane/1523991-widthsegmentcount"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnplane/1522889-heightsegmentcount"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnplane/1524234-cornersegmentcount"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " properties. A higher segment count produces more vertices, which can improve rendering quality for certain lighting models or custom shader effects, but at a cost to rendering performance. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
